OL,3,CChancellor 'must raise taxes to help
OL,4,Cplug #40bn-plus gap to meet fiscal
OL,5,Crule'
OL,7,FProfessor Stephen Millard, Niesr's
OL,8,Fdeputy director for macroeconomics,
OL,9,Fsaid: "With growth at only 1.3% and
OL,10,Finflation above target, things are not
OL,11,Flooking good for the Chancellor, who
OL,12,Fwill need to either raise taxes or
OL,13,Freduce spending or both in the October
OL,14,Fbudget if she is to meet her fiscal
OL,15,Frules."
OL,17,FDespite the inflation pressures, Niesr
OL,18,Fexpects the Bank of England to cut
OL,19,Finterest rates from 4.25% currently to
OL,20,F3.5% at the beginning of 2026.
